OL,6,FCouncil tax is typically up #109 a
OL,7,Fyear; car tax is going up to #195 and
OL,8,FEVs are no longer exempt; water bills
OL,9,F- typically #123 more, and energy
OL,10,Fbills averaging #159 more.
OL,12,FFor some, this onslaught of household
OL,13,Fprice rises will be off-set to some
OL,14,Fextent by increases in benefits,
OL,15,Fpensions and minimum wage. But forget
OL,16,Fthe usual April showers - what's
OL,17,Fcoming for millions is a deluge of
OL,18,Fhigher bills.
